By: Howard County Senators
Introduced and read first time: January 28, 2025
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Howard County – Department of Planning and Zoning – Parking Space
3 Requirements for New Construction
4 Ho. Co. 13–25
5 FOR the purpose of requiring the Howard County Department of Planning and Zoning to
6 consider whether pedestrian infrastructure could offset the need for the construction
7 of parking spaces for new construction when determining the minimum number of
8 mandatory parking spaces; and generally relating to requirements for the Howard
9 County Department of Planning and Zoning.
10 BY adding to
11 The Public Local Laws of Howard County
12 Section 3.107
13 Article 14 – Public Local Laws of Maryland
14 (1997 Edition and October 2022 Supplement, as amended)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article 14 – Howard County
18 3.107.
19 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
20 INDICATED.
21 (2) (I) “BUILDING” MEANS A STRUCTURE WITH EXTERIOR WALLS
22 THAT COMBINE TO FORM AN OCCUPIABLE STRUCTURE.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0970*

2 SENATE BILL 970
1 (II) “BUILDING” DOES NOT INCLUDE A TEMPORARY
2 STRUCTURE, AS DEFINED IN THE HOWARD COUNTY BUILDING CODE.
3 (3) “NEW CONSTRUCTION” MEANS CONSTRUCTION OF A BUILDING
4 THAT REQUIRES A HOWARD COUNTY BUILDING PERMIT.
5 (B) WHEN DETERMINING THE MINIMUM NUMBER OF MANDATORY PARKING
6 SPACES FOR NEW CONSTRUCTION, THE HOWARD COUNTY DEPARTMENT OF
7 PLANNING AND ZONING SHALL CONSIDER WHETHER INFRASTRUCTURE FOR
8 PEDESTRIANS COULD OFFSET THE NEED FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF ANY PARKING
9 SPACES FOR THE NEW CONSTRUCTION.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2025.

